# Summary of K2 Program GO20002

Title: Searching for planets around young stars in synergy with HARPS-N

PI: Desidera, Silvano ()
CoIs: M. Damasso, S. Benatti, I. Carleo, V. D'Orazi, R. Gratton and the GAPS team

We propose to observe in Campaign 20 a sample of 218 targets, which are members or candidate members of the Taurus star forming region or its extended halo of slightly older age (Taurus-Ext association). A sub-sample of the targets, including any planet candidate, will be observed using HARPS-N and GIANO-B combined in the GIARPS mode at TNG, in the framework of the GAPS program. The observations will provide clues on the frequency of hot Jupiters around young stars, a refined census of Taurus members after Gaia DR2 selection, and an in-depth study of the variability pattern of young stars due to accretion and magnetic activity.
